description: NPR identified two Trump staffers involved in an altercation at Arlington National Cemetery including a deputy campaign manager, highlighting a disconnect between Trump's messaging and his campaign.
title: Trump deputy campaign manager identified in Arlington National Cemetery dustup

description: Season 4 brings a fresh influx of guest talent to Only Murders in the Building — but the new faces don’t outshine the crimefighting, podcasting stars: Steve Martin, Martin Short and Selena Gomez.
title: The real ‘Only Murders’ crime is that it hasn’t won more Emmys

description: Tribal leaders selected Nga Wai Hono i te Po as the new monarch after the death of her father last week. The second-ever Maori queen takes on the largely ceremonial role at a complicated moment.
title: A 27-year-old just became queen of New Zealand's Maori

description: Morgan led the U.S. to two FIFA Women's World Cup titles and an Olympic gold medal. At age 35, she has now bid farewell to a career that she said was "more than I could have ever dreamed of."
title: Alex Morgan, the face of American soccer for a generation, says she will retire

description: Athletes who contracted childhood polio share their stories of how they overcame the consequences of the disease — and what sports means to them.
title: Paralympians who faced polio: lovey-dovey table tennis duo, fierce wheelchair racer

description: Athletes who contracted childhood polio share their stories of how they overcame the consequences of the disease — and what sports means to them.
title: Sports brought hope -- and love -- to these Paralympians who had childhood polio

description: Viral stardom is often a prison — but on the dazzling and frequently hilarious Alligator Bites Never Heal, the "Yucky Blucky Fruitcake" rapper proves those walls can't contain her talent.
title: Doechii is too big for your small screen

description: Scholar, historian, artist and raconteur Nell Irvin Painter is the author of The History of White People and Old in Art School. Her latest book is an insightful addition to her canon.
title: 'I Just Keep Talking' is a refreshing and wide-ranging essay collection

description: On Never Gets Late Here, Shenseea takes the scope of dancehall even higher. And, yet, the Jamaican singer tells NPR that she's already looking forward: “Just look out for new music. We’re not stopping."
title: Shenseea’s not done experimenting with dancehall's pop future
